cc:Work.dc:title: Colour Clock
cc:Work.dc:description:
An animated clock using colours. The hour, minute, and second regions expose a small part of the underneath shaded gradient, creating a display that looks a bit like a normal clock, but uses blended colours rather than numbers (red = 12, yellow = 3, green = 6, blue = 9).

My idea was that this might help younger children to tell the time without having to know what numbers mean (e.g. it's yellow and orange).

[Update frequency is 200ms, but can be changed by editing the changeTime timeout at the end of the changeTime function.]
